'''MaKami College''' is a provincially credited [[List of colleges in Alberta|private college in Alberta]] that trains students to become [[Massage therapists|licensed massage therapists]]. Established in Edmonton, AB in 2001 by the Pavkovik Family.

== History ==

MaKami College was founded in 2001 in [[Edmonton]], AB. It started as a small [[vocational college]] and has since grown to an enrollment of over 200 students per year. A second campus was opened in [[Calgary]], AB in 2013. In 2014 MaKami College was listed on Profit Guide's Profit 500 - Canada's Fastest Growing Companies list.<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 Profit 500|url=http://www.profitguide.com/microsite/profit500/2014|website=ProfitGuide.com|publisher=Profit Guide|accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref>

== Accreditation ==

MaKami College is a member in good standing with [http://www.nhpcanada.org/ NHP Canada], [http://www.csmta.ca/index.html Canadian Sports Massage Therapists Association] and the Better Business Bureau.<ref>{{cite web|title=Better Business Bureau|url=http://www.bbb.org/edmonton/business-reviews/massage-school/makami-college-of-massage-therapy-in-edmonton-ab-165243|publisher=Better Business Bureau|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref>

== Edmonton Campus ==

The Edmonton Campus and Head Office of MaKami College is located on the second floor of [[Capilano Mall]], across from the [[Edmonton Public Library]]. With the announced demolition of the Capilano Mall,<ref>{{cite news|last=Maimann|first=Kevin|title=Stores in Capilano Mall in Edmonton Close the Doors|url=http://www.edmontonsun.com/2013/06/09/stores-in-capilano-mall-in-edmonton-close-the-doors|accessdate=27 August 2013|newspaper=The Edmonton Sun|date=June 9, 2013}}</ref> MaKami College will be moving the campus to another location. Second year students are already being relocated to the new Sports Massage Facility Centre off 50 Street & 106 Ave.<ref>{{cite web|title=Makami Edmonton Campus Expands|url=http://makamicollege.com/news/2013/jun/14/makami-edmonton-campus-expands/|work=MaKami College|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref> The Edmonton campus houses first and second year massage therapy students as well as workshops for students and working RMTs.

== Calgary Campus ==

Opened in 2013, the Calgary campus is located at 9618 Horton Rd SW, Calgary, AB. Enrollment in the Calgary massage therapy courses has been growing and the college has called their expansion a "success".<ref>{{cite web|title=MaKami Massage Therapy College Celebrates Success in Calgary|url=http://www.wireservice.ca/index.php?module=News&func=display&sid=11899|website=Wireservice.ca|publisher=Wire Service|accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref>

== Community Involvement ==

Since 2001, MaKami College has been very involved in the community by sponsoring charity events and helping recent immigrants get skills and confidence to enhance job opportunities. MaKami College's managing director, Marija Pavkovic Tovissi, is also the founder of the [http://queenesther.ca/ Queen Esther Foundation] which helps recent immigrants with their ESL skills and assists with helping them find and secure employment opportunities. "MaKami and Queen Esther were both my dreams, and to see them succeed and have people notice is such a great experience."<ref>{{cite news|title=Edmonton Businesswoman Recognized in International Magazine|url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/edmonton-businesswoman-recognized-international-magazine-133000177.html|accessdate=4 August 2014|work=Yahoo! Finance|agency=Red Queen Creative|publisher=Yahoo!|date=6 February 2014}}</ref>

